	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jul 13th 5:16 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I really wish people wouldn't comment on things they know nothing about...<br><br>I'm about 90% sure you've never used this item, since first of all, you don't take the full damage from the proc (unless of course you're running around with minimum MResist, in which case, I hope it does kill you since you're a buffoon). When I use it, with my 49 Mresist, I take 47 points per proc, while the mob takes the full 75. Occasionally, and I say occasionally since I have yet to master avoiding the full proc, I can minimize the proc damage on me down to about 10 to 15 points.<br><br>Now...youre telling me, even at 75x3 self-damage (225), and you with at least 700 hit points at level 30 (leaving you with 475), while you're delivering an avg of 3 45 to 60 point hits from the stick's impact itself, and delivering at least 50 points per flying kick (that's 200 points per attack round), that this weapon is impractical? <br><br>And you're other points are totally moot if you're in a competent group. The tank's job is to take hits. If they're not, then YOU'RE the idiot for not finding another tank to replace them. The cleric's job is to heal. If they're not, then YOU'RE the idiot for not finding another healer to replace them. If you're a monk and you're tanking when there's a tank in your group, then, you guessed it, YOU'RE AN IDIOT. <br><br>If you're soloing however, then your argument may hold water as far as downtime is concerned.<br><br>A proc that hurts you is bad? So its bad when it hurts your target more??&nbsp;&nbsp;Are you on crack?<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Yuron Krakk<br>Troll Extraordinaire</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
